      <!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
        The topic covers the overview of the deployment method.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    The deployment procedure of &productnameshort; comprises three phases. Do
    not skip any of the phases and follow the order as stated below.
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem condition="dasd">
      <para>
        DASD disks activation&mdash;before you start the deployment, you need
        to ensure that all disks to be used are available and active. For
        details, refer to
        <xref linkend="deployment-raw-ibmz-dasd-preparing-machine"/>        .
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem condition="zfcp">
      <para>
        Ensure that all disk are available and active. For details, refer to <xref linkend="deployment-raw-ibmz-zfcd"/>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Preparing a configuration device&mdash;to configure the network, add
        users and register the system, prepare the configuration according to
        the instructions provided in
        <xref linkend="deployment-raw-ibmz-dasd-preparing-configuration"/>.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Downloading the &productnameshort; image and deploying it on the disk.
        For details, refer to
        <xref linkend="deployment-raw-ibmz-dasd-deploying-image"/>.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
</topic>
